<p>
The <b>alternating algebra</b> \(\Alt^\bullet(V)\)
(where \(V\) has dimension \(n\)) is
\[\Alt^\bullet(V) := \bigoplus_{k= 0}^n\Alt^k(V)\]
where \(\Alt^0(V) = \mathbf F,\;\Alt^1(V) = V,\;
\Alt^k(V) = \{x_1\wedge\cdots\wedge x_k : x_i\in V\}\) are the
<b>alternating powers</b> of \(V\).
</p>
<p>
Here, \(\wedge\) is the <a knowl="defs/vec/wedge">wedge product</a>.
</p>
<p>
Related: <a knowl="defs/vec/tensor-alg">tensor algebra</a>.
</p>
</body>
</html>
